Return information about vendor.
 This is typically a ASCII readable string such as

Retrieve more elaborate information about caches (as opposed

 set size, line size etc. for each level of the cache hierarchy.

defs.name: has_sse3
defs.docs: Streaming SIMD Extensions 3 (SSE3). A value of 1 indicates the processor supports this technology.

defs.name: has_pclmulqdq
defs.docs: PCLMULQDQ. A value of 1 indicates the processor supports the PCLMULQDQ instruction

defs.name: has_ds_area
defs.docs: 64-bit DS Area. A value of 1 indicates the processor supports DS area using 64-bit layout

defs.name: has_monitor_mwait
defs.docs: MONITOR/MWAIT. A value of 1 indicates the processor supports this feature.

defs.name: has_cpl
defs.docs: CPL Qualified Debug Store. A value of 1 indicates the processor supports the extensions to the  Debug Store feature to allow for branch message storage qualified by CPL.

defs.name: has_vmx
defs.docs: Virtual Machine Extensions. A value of 1 indicates that the processor supports this technology.

defs.name: has_smx
defs.docs: Safer Mode Extensions. A value of 1 indicates that the processor supports this technology. See Chapter 5, Safer Mode Extensions Reference.

defs.name: has_eist
defs.docs: Enhanced Intel SpeedStepÂ® technology. A value of 1 indicates that the processor supports this technology.

defs.name: has_tm2
defs.docs: Thermal Monitor 2. A value of 1 indicates whether the processor supports this technology.

defs.name: has_ssse3
defs.docs: A value of 1 indicates the presence of the Supplemental Streaming SIMD Extensions 3 (SSSE3). A value of 0 indicates the instruction extensions are not present in the processor

defs.name: has_cnxtid
defs.docs: L1 Context ID. A value of 1 indicates the L1 data cache mode can be set to either adaptive mode or shared mode. A value of 0 indicates this feature is not supported. See definition of the IA32_MISC_ENABLE MSR Bit 24 (L1 Data Cache Context Mode) for details.

defs.name: has_fma
defs.docs: A value of 1 indicates the processor supports FMA extensions using YMM state.

defs.name: has_cmpxchg16b
defs.docs: CMPXCHG16B Available. A value of 1 indicates that the feature is available. See the CMPXCHG8B/CMPXCHG16B Compare and Exchange Bytes section. 14

defs.name: has_pdcm
defs.docs: Perfmon and Debug Capability: A value of 1 indicates the processor supports the performance   and debug feature indication MSR IA32_PERF_CAPABILITIES.

defs.name: has_pcid
defs.docs: Process-context identifiers. A value of 1 indicates that the processor supports PCIDs and the software may set CR4.PCIDE to 1.

defs.name: has_dca
defs.docs: A value of 1 indicates the processor supports the ability to prefetch data from a memory mapped device.

defs.name: has_sse41
defs.docs: A value of 1 indicates that the processor supports SSE4.1.

defs.name: has_sse42
defs.docs: A value of 1 indicates that the processor supports SSE4.2.

defs.name: has_x2apic
defs.docs: A value of 1 indicates that the processor supports x2APIC feature.

defs.name: has_movbe
defs.docs: A value of 1 indicates that the processor supports MOVBE instruction.

defs.name: has_popcnt
defs.docs: A value of 1 indicates that the processor supports the POPCNT instruction.

defs.name: has_tsc_deadline
defs.docs: A value of 1 indicates that the processors local APIC timer supports one-shot operation using a TSC deadline value.

defs.name: has_aesni
defs.docs: A value of 1 indicates that the processor supports the AESNI instruction extensions.

defs.name: has_xsave
defs.docs: A value of 1 indicates that the processor supports the XSAVE/XRSTOR processor extended states feature, the XSETBV/XGETBV instructions, and XCR0.

defs.name: has_oxsave
defs.docs: A value of 1 indicates that the OS has enabled XSETBV/XGETBV instructions to access XCR0, and support for processor extended state management using XSAVE/XRSTOR.

defs.name: has_avx
defs.docs: A value of 1 indicates the processor supports the AVX instruction extensions.

defs.name: has_f16c
defs.docs: A value of 1 indicates that processor supports 16-bit floating-point conversion instructions.

defs.name: has_rdrand
defs.docs: A value of 1 indicates that processor supports RDRAND instruction.

defs.name: has_fpu
defs.docs: Floating Point Unit On-Chip. The processor contains an x87 FPU.

defs.name: has_vme
defs.docs: Virtual 8086 Mode Enhancements. Virtual 8086 mode enhancements, including CR4.VME for controlling the feature, CR4.PVI for protected mode virtual interrupts, software interrupt indirection, expansion of the TSS with the software indirection bitmap, and EFLAGS.VIF and EFLAGS.VIP flags.

defs.name: has_de
defs.docs: Debugging Extensions. Support for I/O breakpoints, including CR4.DE for controlling the feature, and optional trapping of accesses to DR4 and DR5.

defs.name: has_pse
defs.docs: Page Size Extension. Large pages of size 4 MByte are supported, including CR4.PSE for controlling the feature, the defined dirty bit in PDE (Page Directory Entries), optional reserved bit trapping in CR3, PDEs, and PTEs.

defs.name: has_tsc
defs.docs: Time Stamp Counter. The RDTSC instruction is supported, including CR4.TSD for controlling privilege.

defs.name: has_msr
defs.docs: Model Specific Registers RDMSR and WRMSR Instructions. The RDMSR and WRMSR instructions are supported. Some of the MSRs are implementation dependent.

defs.name: has_pae
defs.docs: Physical Address Extension. Physical addresses greater than 32 bits are supported: extended page table entry formats, an extra level in the page translation tables is defined, 2-MByte pages are supported instead of 4 Mbyte pages if PAE bit is 1.

defs.name: has_mce
defs.docs: Machine Check Exception. Exception 18 is defined for Machine Checks, including CR4.MCE for controlling the feature. This feature does not define the model-specific implementations of machine-check error logging, reporting, and processor shutdowns. Machine Check exception handlers may have to depend on processor version to do model specific processing of the exception, or test for the presence of the Machine Check feature.

defs.name: has_cmpxchg8b
defs.docs: CMPXCHG8B Instruction. The compare-and-exchange 8 bytes (64 bits) instruction is supported (implicitly locked and atomic).

defs.name: has_apic
defs.docs: APIC On-Chip. The processor contains an Advanced Programmable Interrupt Controller (APIC), responding to memory mapped commands in the physical address range FFFE0000H to FFFE0FFFH (by default - some processors permit the APIC to be relocated).

defs.name: has_sysenter_sysexit
defs.docs: SYSENTER and SYSEXIT Instructions. The SYSENTER and SYSEXIT and associated MSRs are supported.

defs.name: has_mtrr
defs.docs: Memory Type Range Registers. MTRRs are supported. The MTRRcap MSR contains feature bits that describe what memory types are supported, how many variable MTRRs are supported, and whether fixed MTRRs are supported.

defs.name: has_pge
defs.docs: Page Global Bit. The global bit is supported in paging-structure entries that map a page, indicating TLB entries that are common to different processes and need not be flushed. The CR4.PGE bit controls this feature.

defs.name: has_mca
defs.docs: Machine Check Architecture. A value of 1 indicates the Machine Check Architecture of reporting machine errors is supported. The MCG_CAP MSR contains feature bits describing how many banks of error reporting MSRs are supported.

defs.name: has_cmov
defs.docs: Conditional Move Instructions. The conditional move instruction CMOV is supported. In addition, if x87 FPU is present as indicated by the CPUID.FPU feature bit, then the FCOMI and FCMOV instructions are supported

defs.name: has_pat
defs.docs: Page Attribute Table. Page Attribute Table is supported. This feature augments the Memory Type Range Registers (MTRRs), allowing an operating system to specify attributes of memory accessed through a linear address on a 4KB granularity.

defs.name: has_pse36
defs.docs: 36-Bit Page Size Extension. 4-MByte pages addressing physical memory beyond 4 GBytes are supported with 32-bit paging. This feature indicates that upper bits of the physical address of a 4-MByte page are encoded in bits 20:13 of the page-directory entry. Such physical addresses are limited by MAXPHYADDR and may be up to 40 bits in size.

defs.name: has_psn
defs.docs: Processor Serial Number. The processor supports the 96-bit processor identification number feature and the feature is enabled.

defs.name: has_clflush
defs.docs: CLFLUSH Instruction. CLFLUSH Instruction is supported.

defs.name: has_ds
defs.docs: Debug Store. The processor supports the ability to write debug information into a memory resident buffer. This feature is used by the branch trace store (BTS) and processor event-based sampling (PEBS) facilities (see Chapter 23, Introduction to Virtual-Machine Extensions, in the IntelÂ® 64 and IA-32 Architectures Software Developers Manual, Volume 3C).

defs.name: has_acpi
defs.docs: Thermal Monitor and Software Controlled Clock Facilities. The processor implements internal MSRs that allow processor temperature to be monitored and processor performance to be modulated in predefined duty cycles under software control.

defs.name: has_mmx
defs.docs: Intel MMX Technology. The processor supports the Intel MMX technology.

defs.name: has_fxsave_fxstor
defs.docs: FXSAVE and FXRSTOR Instructions. The FXSAVE and FXRSTOR instructions are supported for fast save and restore of the floating point context. Presence of this bit also indicates that CR4.OSFXSR is available for an operating system to indicate that it supports the FXSAVE and FXRSTOR instructions.

defs.name: has_sse
defs.docs: SSE. The processor supports the SSE extensions.

defs.name: has_sse2
defs.docs: SSE2. The processor supports the SSE2 extensions.

defs.name: has_ss
defs.docs: Self Snoop. The processor supports the management of conflicting memory types by performing a snoop of its own cache structure for transactions issued to the bus.

defs.name: has_htt
defs.docs: Max APIC IDs reserved field is Valid. A value of 0 for HTT indicates there is only a single logical processor in the package and software should assume only a single APIC ID is reserved.  A value of 1 for HTT indicates the value in CPUID.1.EBX\[23:16\] (the Maximum number of addressable IDs for logical processors in this package) is valid for the package.

defs.name: has_tm
defs.docs: Thermal Monitor. The processor implements the thermal monitor automatic thermal control circuitry (TCC).

defs.name: has_pbe
defs.docs: Pending Break Enable. The processor supports the use of the FERR#/PBE# pin when the processor is in the stop-clock state (STPCLK# is asserted) to signal the processor that an interrupt is pending and that the processor should return to normal operation to handle the interrupt. Bit 10 (PBE enable) in the IA32_MISC_ENABLE MSR enables this capability.

defs.name: max_cores_for_package

defs.name: coherency_line_size
defs.docs: System Coherency Line Size (Bits 11-00)

defs.name: physical_line_partitions
defs.docs: Physical Line partitions (Bits 21-12)

defs.name: associativity
defs.docs: Ways of associativity (Bits 31-22)

defs.name: sets
defs.docs: Number of Sets (Bits 31-00)

defs.name: is_write_back_invalidate
defs.docs:
Write-Back Invalidate/Invalidate (Bit 0)
 False: WBINVD/INVD from threads sharing this cache acts upon lower level caches for threads sharing this cache.
 True: WBINVD/INVD is not guaranteed to act upon lower level caches of non-originating threads sharing this cache.

defs.name: is_inclusive
defs.docs:
Cache Inclusiveness (Bit 1)
 False: Cache is not inclusive of lower cache levels.
 True: Cache is inclusive of lower cache levels.

defs.name: has_complex_indexing
defs.docs:
Complex Cache Indexing (Bit 2)
 False: Direct mapped cache.
 True: A complex function is used to index the cache, potentially using all address bits.

defs.docs: Smallest monitor-line size in bytes (default is processor's monitor granularity)

defs.name: largest_monitor_line
defs.docs: Largest monitor-line size in bytes (default is processor's monitor granularity

defs.name: supported_c7_states
defs.docs: Number of C7 sub C-states supported using MWAIT (Bits 31 - 28)

defs.name: has_arat
defs.docs: ARAT. APIC-Timer-always-running feature is supported if set.

defs.name: has_pln
defs.docs: PLN. Power limit notification controls are supported if set.

defs.name: has_ecmd
defs.docs: ECMD. Clock modulation duty cycle extension is supported if set.

defs.name: has_ptm

defs.name: has_hwp
defs.docs: HWP. HWP base registers (IA32_PM_ENABLE[bit 0], IA32_HWP_CAPABILITIES, IA32_HWP_REQUEST, IA32_HWP_STATUS) are supported if set.

defs.name: has_hwp_notification

defs.name: has_hwp_activity_window

defs.name: has_hwp_energy_performance_preference

defs.name: has_hwp_package_level_request
defs.docs: HWP Package Level Request. IA32_HWP_REQUEST_PKG MSR is supported if set.

defs.name: has_hdc
defs.docs: HDC. HDC base registers IA32_PKG_HDC_CTL, IA32_PM_CTL1, IA32_THREAD_STALL MSRs are supported if set.

defs.name: has_turbo_boost3
defs.docs: IntelÂ® Turbo Boost Max Technology 3.0 available.

defs.name: has_hwp_capabilities
defs.docs: HWP Capabilities. Highest Performance change is supported if set.

defs.name: has_hwp_peci_override
defs.docs: HWP PECI override is supported if set.

defs.name: has_flexible_hwp
defs.docs: Flexible HWP is supported if set.

defs.name: has_hwp_fast_access_mode
defs.docs: Fast access mode for the IA32_HWP_REQUEST MSR is supported if set.

defs.name: has_ignore_idle_processor_hwp_request
defs.docs: Ignoring Idle Logical Processor HWP request is supported if set.

defs.name: has_hw_coord_feedback
defs.docs: Hardware Coordination Feedback Capability (Presence of IA32_MPERF and IA32_APERF). The capability to provide a measure of delivered processor performance (since last reset of the counters), as a percentage of expected processor performance at frequency specified in CPUID Brand String Bits 02 - 01

defs.name: has_energy_bias_pref
defs.docs: The processor supports performance-energy bias preference if CPUID.06H:ECX.SETBH[bit 3] is set and it also implies the presence of a new architectural MSR called IA32_ENERGY_PERF_BIAS (1B0H)

defs.name: has_fsgsbase

Gives detailed information about the current level in the topology
 (how many cores, what type etc.).

defs.name: processors
defs.docs:
Number of logical processors at this level type.
 The number reflects configuration as shipped.

defs.docs: Level number.

defs.docs: x2APIC ID the current logical processor. (Bits 31-00)

defs.name: shift_right_for_next_apic_id
defs.docs:
Number of bits to shift right on x2APIC ID to get a unique topology ID of the next level type. (Bits 04-00)
 All logical processors with the same next level ID share current level.

defs.docs:
The size in bytes (from the offset specified in EBX) of the save area
 for an extended state feature associated with a valid sub-leaf index, n.
 This field reports 0 if the sub-leaf index, n, is invalid.

defs.name: offset
defs.docs:
The offset in bytes of this extended state components save area

defs.name: is_in_ia32_xss
defs.docs:
True if the bit n (corresponding to the sub-leaf index)

defs.name: is_in_xcr0

defs.name: is_compacted_format
defs.docs:
Returns true when the compacted format of an XSAVE area is used,
 this extended state component located on the next 64-byte
 boundary following the preceding state component
 (otherwise, it is located immediately following the preceding state component).
